com.code.aon.common.event
Class ManagerBeanVetoListenerSupport

java.lang.Object
  com.code.aon.common.event.ManagerBeanVetoListenerSupport
All Implemented Interfaces:
IManagerBeanVetoListener
public class ManagerBeanVetoListenerSupport
extends java.lang.Object
implements IManagerBeanVetoListener

This is a utility class that can be used by IManagerBean classes that support CRUD vetoable operations. You can use an instance of this class as a member field of your bean and delegate various work to it.

addListener

public void addListener(IManagerBeanVetoListener listener)
Add a IManagerBeanVetoListener to the listener list. The same listener object may be added more than once, and will be called as many times as it is added.

Parameters:
listener -

removeListener

public void removeListener(IManagerBeanVetoListener listener)
Remove a IManagerBeanVetoListener from the listener list. This removes a IManagerBeanListener that was registered. If listener was added more than once to the same event source, it will be notified one less time after being removed.

Parameters:
listener -
